WFTO-Europe is one of the five regional branches of the World Fair Trade Organization global network, the other four being: WFTO-Africa, WFTO-Asia (World Fair Trade Organization - Asia), WFTO-LA (World Fair Trade Organization – Latin America) and WFTO Pacific Rim. Together, the five WFTO regional networks come together as regional chapters to represent more than 300 members within 70 countries worldwide, that are committed 100% to Fair Trade and its principles.&#xd;
&#xd;
For a detailed view on the WFTO global network, its members and structure, please visit WFTO global website at: http://www.wfto.com/ &#xd;
&#xd;
At European level, WFTO-Europe is a member organization of the Fair Trade Advocacy Office (FTAO) in Brussels. The FTAO is a joint initiative of World Fair Trade Organization (WFTO), WFTO–Europe and Fairtrade International (FI). Through these three networks the FTAO represents an estimate of  2.5 million Fair Trade producers and workers from 70 countries, 24 labelling initiatives, over 500 specialised Fair Trade importers, 4.000 World Shops and more than 100.000 volunteers. The Fair Trade Advocacy Office speaks out for Fair Trade and trade justice with the aim to improve the livelihoods of marginalised producers and workers, especially in the South. &#xd;
&#xd;
For a detailed view on the FTAO’s activities, please visit its website at: http://www.fairtrade-advocacy.org/&#xd;
&#xd;
WFTO-Europe is also a member of the "Federation of European &amp; International associations based in Belgium" (FAIB) and actively contribute to the Fair Trade Towns Campaign.
